Pedalator assessment of occlusive arterial disease of the lower extremities. Use of the Pedalator instead of the treadmill in the assessment of occlusive arterial disease of the lower extremities has been evaluated. The following aspects were assessed: (1) The effect on the cardiovascular system in terms of brachial arterial pressure, pulse rate, and oxygen consumption (VO2) during exercise in 5 health volunteers (2) emg activity of the tibialis anterior and gastrocnemius muscles during exercise in the same 5 volunteers